  <description><![CDATA[<p>The traditional Hotel Intermonti is set back from the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89}" title="Livigno">Livigno</a>, offering you peaceful panoramic views of the ski area and valley. The interconnecting chalets are a great option if you are looking for cosy accommodation with great access to the ski area.</p>
<h2>Close to the lifts</h2>
<p>Surrounded by a wooded area, the Intermonti offers incredible views of the valley and Livigno's sunny slopes. The closest lift, which goes to the Mottolino side of the mountain, is located about 100 metres from the hotel. To venture further afield, simply hop on the resort bus that takes you to Livigno's other lifts. In addition, you can take the same bus to the resort's centre, where you can make the most of the bustling bars, welcoming restaurants, and shops.</p>
<h2>Great facilities</h2>
<p>The 140-room hotel is made up of four traditional style buildings, the spacious bedrooms are all furnished in a traditional alpine style with warm wood throughout.  The hotel has some lovely facilities you can make the most of during your holiday. Children have their own playroom to enjoy while adults can head up to the bar and enjoy a few drinks while playing a game of pool.</p>
<p>Meals are served buffet style, each morning you can get ready for an active day on the slopes at the breakfast buffet and when you return you can enjoy a tasty buffet style meal often including classic Italian dishes.</p>
<h2>Relaxation</h2>
<p>If you're in need of some relaxation, the spa is a great place to be. You can enjoy having a dip in the pool or give your achy ski legs a break in the sauna and Turkish bath. If you want to stay active there is also a fitness room with a range of equipment available. There is a local fee to enter but it is well worth it for a moment of relaxation. </p>]]></description>
